Ebola outbreak 30 km [18.6 mi] from Beni: Already 20 suspicious deaths
-------------------------------------------
The 10th Ebola outbreak was declared on Wed 1 Aug 2018 in the DRC. According to data from the Ministry of Health, 26 cases of fever with hemorrhagic signs, including 20 deaths, were reported in the health area of Mangina located in the health zone of Mabalako, Beni territory, in the province of North Kivu.

Of the 6 samples analyzed on Tue 31 Jul 2018 and analyzed by the National Institute for Biomedical Research (INRB), 4 were positive for Ebola Virus Disease (EVD). The strain of the virus is not yet determined, and the link between this new outbreak and that declared over in Equateur province is not (yet) determined.

"A team of 12 experts from the Ministry of Health based in Kinshasa will arrive in Beni this Thu 2 Aug 2018 to put in place the various components of the response. This team of laboratory technicians, epidemiologists, clinical psychologists, and doctors for medical care will carry a mobile laboratory of the INRB and personal protective equipment," says a statement from the Ministry of Health that adds it will take all useful provisions "to quickly and effectively contain this new EVD epidemic."

The Congolese government declared on Tue 24 Jul 2018 the end of the EVD epidemic that officially broke out on Tue 8 May 2018 in the Province of Ecuador. A total of 54 cases were identified, including 33 deaths and 21 survivors.

